 16334a82-9687-42f6-9c7a-4fd534aa7f22.a34dd3df-fc90-4cd2-af24-e89a16c836f3.description=Purpose\: 
 Set multiple database options in one step. This step evaluates a comma-delimited list of option and value pairs, and sets the various database options. This step can be run on the Instance and Database level. If run on the Instance level, the Database Name parameter cannot be blank.
 
 Valid Options (Option {Values})\:
 
 DB State\: 
 (ONLINE,OFFLINE,EMERGENCY {<blank>})
 
 User Access\:
 (SINGLE_USER,RESTRICTED_USER,MULTI_USER {<blank>})
 
 DB Update\:
 (READ_ONLY,READ_WRITE {<blank>})
 
 External Access\:
 (DB_CHAINING {ON,OFF})
 (TRUSTWORTHY {ON,OFF})
 
 Cursor\:
 (CURSOR_CLOSE_ON_COMMIT {ON,OFF}) 
 (CURSOR_DEFAULT {LOCAL,GLOBAL}) 
 
 Auto\:
 (AUTO_CLOSE {ON,OFF}) 
 (AUTO_CREATE_STATISTICS {ON,OFF}) 
 (AUTO_SHRINK {ON,OFF}) 
 (AUTO_UPDATE_STATISTICS {ON,OFF}) 
 (AUTO_UPDATE_STATISTICS_ASYNC {ON,OFF})
 
 SQL\:
 (ANSI_NULL_DEFAULT {ON,OFF}) 
 (ANSI_NULLS {ON,OFF}) 
 (ANSI_PADDING {ON,OFF}) 
 (ANSI_WARNINGS {ON,OFF}) 
 (ARITHABORT {ON,OFF}) 
 (CONCAT_NULL_YIELDS_NULL {ON,OFF}) 
 (NUMERIC_ROUNDABORT {ON,OFF}) 
 (QUOTED_IDENTIFIER {ON,OFF}) 
 (RECURSIVE_TRIGGERS {ON,OFF}) 
 
 Recovery\:
 (RECOVERY {FULL,BULK_LOGGED,SIMPLE}) 
 (TORN_PAGE_DETECTION {ON,OFF})
 (PAGE_VERIFY {CHECKSUM,TORN_PAGE_DETECTION,NONE})
 
 Date Correlation Optimization\:
 (DATE_CORRELATION_OPTIMIZATION {ON,OFF})
 
 Parameterization\:
 (PARAMETERIZATION {SIMPLE,FORCED})
 
 Example valid parameter input\:
 RECOVERY,BULK_LOGGED,SINGLE_USER,,ANSI_NULLS,ON


Inputs\:
 command - executes MSSQLSetDatabaseOptions.py
 Database Name - Database to have options changed. *Required (if Instance-level),String. At Database level, default is current database.
 Instance Account - No description
 Instance Password - No description
 Option and Value List - Comma-delimited list of options and associated values. Optional, String. Acceptable options and values in step description. Format \= <option1>,<value1>,<option2>,<value2>,...
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 Creates a new database on the target Instance. Run MS SQL\: Kill Processes and MS SQL\: Drop Database if replacing an existing database.
 

Inputs\:
 command - executes MSSQLCreateDatabase.py
 Collation - Collation setting of new database. Optional, String. If blank, server default used.
 Compatibility Level - Forces compatibility with behavior of previous SQL Server version. Optional, String. If blank, the server default used. Acceptable values \= [<blank>,60,65,70,80,90]
 Data File Filegroups - Comma-delimited list of filegroup(s) associated with data files. Optional, String. Blank values in list replaced with "PRIMARY"
 Data File Paths - Comma-delimited list of data files. Optional, String. Blank values in list replaced with path\: <server default data directory>\<dbname>[file\#].mdf. Acceptable values in list \= directory paths, file paths, filenames, or blanks, in any combination.
 Data File Sizes, Growths, and Max Sizes - Comma-delimited list of sizing information for each data file. Optional, String. Blank values in list replaced with server defaults (3MB,1MB,0), depending on corresponding value. Values in list are initial size, growth increment, and max size, in that order. First 3 values in list apply to first data file, while next 3 apply to the next data file, and so on. Sizes expressed as [integer][KB,MB,GB], growth rates expressed as [integer][KB,MB,GB,%] or 0 (unlimited).
 Database Name - Name of new database. *Required, String.
 Instance Account - No description
 Instance Password - No description
 Log File Path - Directory path, file path, or filename for log file. Optional, String. If blank, replaced with path <server default log directory>\<dbname>_log.mdf. Acceptable values \= directory path (filename <DBname>_log.ldf used), file path, filename (default log directory used), or blank.
 Log File Size, Growth, and Max Size - Comma-delimited list of sizing information for log file. Optional, String. Blank items replaced with server defaults (3MB,1%,0), depending on corresponding value. The values in list are initial size, growth increment, and max size, in that order.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 16334a82-9687-42f6-9c7a-4fd534aa7f22.description=<pre>
 Description

This workflow creates a new database on the target instance. The only required parameter is "Database Name", but there are several optional parameters to customize the process. 

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Database Name - Name of the new database. *Required, String.
 Database.Name - No description
 Instance.Name - No description
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Server.Name - No description

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Log File Path - Directory path, file path, or filename for log file. Optional, String. If blank, replaced with path \_log.mdf. Acceptable values \= directory path (filename _log.ldf used), file path, filename (default log directory used), or blank.
 Compatibility Level - No description
 Log File Size,Growth,and Max Size - Comma-delimited list of sizing information for log file. Optional, String. Blank items replaced with server defaults (3MB,1%,0), depending on corresponding value. The values in list are initial size, growth increment, and max size, in that order.
 Data Filegroups - Comma-delimited list of filegroup(s) associated with data files. Optional, String. Blank values in list replaced with "PRIMARY".
 Default Database - No description
 Collation - No description
 Drop Database If Exists - Flag database as droppable if found. Optional,String. Acceptable inputs \= YES, NO (default).
 Database Owner Login Name - Login name of owner of the database. Optional, String. Windows authenticated login format\: \
 SQL Instance Password - No description
 SQL Instance Account - No description
 Data File Paths - No description
 Database Recovery Model - Database recovery model. Optional, String. Acceptable values \= [FULL (default),BULK_LOGGED,SIMPLE].
 Additional Database Options and Values - No description
 Database Owner Login Password - The password of new owner of database. *Required (if new SQL login needed), String.
 Instance Password - No description
 Data File Sizes,Growths,and Max Sizes - Comma-delimited list of sizing information for each data file. Optional, String. Blank values in list replaced with server defaults (3MB,1MB,0), depending on corresponding value. Values in list are initial size, growth increment, and max size, in that order. First 3 values in list apply to first data file, while next 3 apply to the next data file, and so on. Sizes expressed as [integer][KB,MB,GB], growth rates expressed as [integer][KB,MB,GB,%] or 0 (unlimited).

 Dependencies

Permissions\:
 - Extended Procedures (XP)
 	- When checking for the default file directories, this workflow requires access to an extended procedure that reads the registry.
 		- This only occurs if a data/log file path is not submitted, and a lookup is required to find the default value.
 - System Stored Procedures (SP)
 - Setting a non-default database owner requires the sp_changedbowner proc.
 - CREATE LOGIN permission 
 - If a non-default database owner is specified, and does not exist, the workflow needs to create the appropriate login.

 Results Verification

Verification options\:
- Enable the "MS Master DB Configuration Info" module, and view the results of the Database monitor "Databases", at the Instance level.
- Restart the collector to discover the new database.
- Manually run the query "SELECT Name from master.dbo.sysdatabases where name \= ''" against the target instance.



 Notification Plan

Custom Email and Alert steps can be added to the workflow to notify the proper contacts regarding success or failures within the workflow.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
</pre>
